Sir Bradley Wiggins has been included in Team Sky's line-up for Sunday's Gent-Wevelgem sprint classic.

Wiggins, the 2012 Tour de France champion, will be joined by fellow Great Britain Olympian Geraint Thomas for the 239-kilometre one-day event in Belgium.

Sir Bradley Wiggins (right) has been included in Team Sky's line-up for  Gent-Wevelgem sprint classic

The 239-kilometre one-day event will take place in Belgium on Sunday

Bernhard Eisel, who won the event in 2010, is also included in an eight-man team along with Christian Knees, Ian Stannard, Andy Fenn, Luke Rowe and Elia Viviani.

Giant-Alpecin's John Degenkolb is the defending champion in Flanders. 

 

